# Cargo.lock is TRACKED (not ignored): a transitive dep (cid -> core2 0.4.0) is
# yanked from crates.io, so CI's fresh resolve fails; committing the lock pins the
# yanked-but-locked version and keeps local-green == CI-green. Library convention
# deviated deliberately for this yank-drift.
# build artifacts and signing keys never ship in the public repo: a built image
# bakes WiFi + MQTT credentials, and priv.pem is the mesh-OTA signing key
firmware/*/build/
firmware/mesh_ota/keys/
